description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/17915/documentation

This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for  'marine electric motor', in the Global geography.;This market connects the supply chain of marine electric motors from their production till the place they are employed and used. Default transportation based on ISIC classification is used for the product. Marine electric engine, is an engine running on electricity, dedicated for a fishing vessel. 

Activity starts after the production of marine electric motor.

Activity ends with the provision of marine electric motor to its relevant consumers.
